I"É!<p>Last week, I discovered a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability in the <a class="highlighted" href="https://dev.monkeytype.com/tribe">dev.monkeytype.com</a> tribe chat, allowing malicious users to inject arbitrary JavaScript script via (1) message and (2) name parameters in the chat room. While the vulnerability is severe, Tribe is currently in an alpha release, so it was a great time to catch and remediate the issue before widespread use. In this post, Iâ€™ll describe how client-side valdiation was evaded by modifying raw web socket requests.</p>

